nodes.description:
#### Docker Hub ***is*** a 
cloud-based repository service **that** allows developers to store, share, and manage Docker container images.
  - Provides a central location for finding and accessing container images.
  - Supports public and private repositories.
  - Enables collaboration and sharing of containerized applications.
  - Integrates with CI/CD pipelines for automated builds and deployments.
  - Offers official images maintained by Docker and community-contributed images.
nodes.title: Docker-hub

nodes.description:
#### Ruby ***is*** a 
dynamic, open-source programming language **that** focuses on simplicity and productivity.
  - It's known for its elegant syntax, which is natural to read and easy to write.
  - Ideal for web development, Ruby has a rich ecosystem of libraries and frameworks, including the popular Ruby on Rails.
nodes.title: Ruby

nodes.description:
#### Node.js ***is*** a 
 runtime environment **that** executes JavaScript code on the server side.
  -  It's non-blocking, event-driven, and ideal for building scalable, 
  - real-time applications.
nodes.title: NodeJs

nodes.description:
#### Ruby on Rails ***is*** a 
web application framework **that** uses Ruby.
  - It follows the MVC (Model-View-Controller) pattern for organized code.
  - Emphasizes convention over configuration and the DRY (Don't Repeat Yourself) principle.
  - Includes many tools to simplify tasks like database management and routing.
  - Ideal for quickly building and deploying web applications.
nodes.title: Ruby on Rails

nodes.description:
#### GitLab ***is*** a 
web-based DevOps lifecycle tool **that** provides a Git repository manager providing CI/CD pipeline features and more.
  - Offers version control, issue tracking, CI/CD pipelines, and more.
  - Supports collaboration with features like code review and merge requests.
  - Provides built-in CI/CD pipelines for automating builds, tests, and deployments.
  - Includes container registry, Kubernetes integration, and monitoring tools.
  - Available in both self-managed and SaaS versions, catering to various development needs.
nodes.title: GitLab
Webhook
nodes.description:
#### Webhook ***is*** a 
way for an application to send real-time data to other services **that** is triggered by specific events.
  - Allows apps to communicate instantly without polling.

nodes.title: MySQL
nodes.description:
#### MySQL ***is*** a 
widely-used open-source relational database management system **that** is known for its reliability and ease of use.
  - It supports standard SQL and a variety of data types.
  - Known for its high performance, scalability, and flexibility.
  - Commonly used for web applications and online transaction processing (OLTP).
  - Includes features like replication, clustering, and strong security measures.
  - Ideal for both small and large-scale applications, from individual projects to large enterprises.

nodes.title: JavaScript
nodes.description:
#### JavaScript ***is*** a 
versatile programming language **that** runs in web browsers.
  - It allows developers to create interactive web pages.
  - Supports event-driven, functional, and imperative programming styles.
  - Widely used for front-end development, often alongside HTML and CSS.
  - Can also be used for server-side development with environments like Node.js.

nodes.title: asdfasdfasdf
nodes.description: **Git** is a free and open source distributed version control system designed to handle everything from small to very large projects with speed and efficiency.

nodes.title: SQL
nodes.description:
#### SQL ***is*** a 
standard language **that** is used to manage and manipulate relational databases.
  - It allows for querying, updating, and managing data.
  - Supports operations like SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE, and more.
  - Used for defining database schemas with commands like CREATE, ALTER, and DROP.
  - Essential for backend development and data analysis.

nodes.title: PostgreSQL
nodes.description:
#### PostgreSQL ***is*** a 
powerful, open-source relational database management system **that** emphasizes extensibility and SQL compliance.
  - It supports advanced data types and performance optimization features.
  - Known for reliability, data integrity, and robust transaction support.
  - Includes features like multi-version concurrency control (MVCC) and point-in-time recovery.
  - Extensible through custom functions, data types, and operators.
  - Ideal for complex applications requiring a reliable and scalable database solution.

nodes.title: Github
nodes.description:
#### GitHub ***is*** a 
web-based platform **that** provides version control and collaboration tools for software development.
  - It uses Git for tracking changes in source code during development.
  - Allows multiple developers to work on projects simultaneously with features like branching and merging.
  - Hosts repositories, where code and documentation can be stored, managed, and shared.
  - Supports issue tracking, project management, and continuous integration/continuous deployment (CI/CD).
  - Facilitates collaboration through pull requests, code reviews, and discussions.

nodes.title: Redis
nodes.description:
#### Redis ***is*** an 
open-source, in-memory data structure store **that** is used as a database, cache, and message broker.
  - Supports various data structures like strings, hashes, lists, sets, and sorted sets.
  - Known for its high performance and low latency.
  - Provides persistence options through snapshots and append-only file (AOF) logs.
  - Supports replication, enabling high availability and scalability.
  - Includes features like Lua scripting, pub/sub messaging, and geospatial indexes.

nodes.title: Docker
nodes.description:
#### Docker ***is*** a 
platform **that** enables developers to automate the deployment of applications inside lightweight, portable containers.
  - Uses containerization to package applications with all dependencies.
  - Ensures consistent environments across development, testing, and production.
  - Allows for scalable and isolated application execution.
  - Simplifies configuration and increases deployment speed.
  - Supports Docker Hub for sharing and managing container images.

nodes.title: GitLab CI/CD
nodes.description:
#### GitLab CI/CD ***is*** a 
built-in feature of GitLab **that** automates the software development lifecycle.
  - Allows you to define CI/CD pipelines using `.gitlab-ci.yml` files.
  - Automates the building, testing, and deployment of code.
  - Supports parallel execution, caching, and artifact handling.
  - Integrates with GitLab's version control and project management tools.
  - Provides detailed logs and metrics for monitoring pipeline performance.
  - Facilitates continuous integration and continuous deployment, improving code quality and delivery speed.

nodes.title: Github Actions
nodes.description:
#### GitHub Actions ***is*** a 
tool **that** automates workflows for software development.
  - Allows you to build, test, and deploy code from GitHub.
  - Uses YAML files to define custom workflows.
  - Triggers actions based on events like pushes and pull requests.
  - Includes pre-built actions and supports custom actions.
  - Helps ensure code quality and consistency through automation.

nodes.title: NGINX
nodes.description:
#### NGINX ***is*** a 
high-performance web server and reverse proxy **that** also functions as an HTTP cache and load balancer.
  - Known for its speed, stability, and low resource consumption.
  - Handles high concurrency with an event-driven, asynchronous architecture.
  - Commonly used for serving static content, load balancing HTTP traffic, and acting as a reverse proxy for web applications.
  - Supports TLS/SSL for secure connections and HTTP/2 for improved performance.
  - Extensible with modules and integrates well with other web technologies.

nodes.title: Nest JS
nodes.description:
#### NestJS ***is*** a 
progressive Node.js framework **that** is used for building efficient, reliable, and scalable server-side applications.
  - Built with TypeScript and fully supports JavaScript.
  - Utilizes modern JavaScript, TypeScript, and design patterns such as MVC and Dependency Injection.
  - Integrates seamlessly with other libraries and frameworks like Express and Fastify.
  - Provides a modular architecture, making it easy to organize and manage code.
  - Supports extensive features such as middleware, authentication, and microservices.
  - Ideal for developing enterprise-grade applications due to its robust set of features and architectural principles.

nodes.title: KOA JS
nodes.description:
#### Koa ***is*** a 
minimalist and flexible Node.js web framework **that** is designed for building APIs and web applications.
  - Developed by the creators of Express, offering a more modern approach.
  - Uses async/await for handling asynchronous operations, making code easier to read and maintain.
  - Provides a lightweight and unopinionated structure, giving developers the freedom to design their application architecture.
  - Does not include middleware by default, allowing developers to choose only the components they need.
  - Ideal for building high-performance and scalable web applications.

nodes.title: JavaScript
nodes.description:
#### JavaScript ***is*** a 
versatile programming language **that** runs in web browsers.
  - It allows developers to create interactive web pages.
  - Supports event-driven, functional, and imperative programming styles.
  - Widely used for front-end development, often alongside HTML and CSS.
  - Can also be used for server-side development with environments like Node.js.

nodes.title: HTML
nodes.description:
#### HTML ***is*** a 
standard markup language **that** is used for creating and structuring web pages.
  - Stands for HyperText Markup Language.
  - Defines the structure of web content using elements like headings, paragraphs, links, images, and lists.
  - Forms the backbone of web development, working in conjunction with CSS and JavaScript.
  - Uses tags to encapsulate different parts of the content, providing semantic meaning.
  - Essential for creating accessible and SEO-friendly web pages.

nodes.title: CSS
nodes.description:
#### CSS ***is*** a 
stylesheet language **that** is used for describing the presentation of a document written in HTML or XML.
  - Stands for Cascading Style Sheets.
  - Controls the layout, colors, fonts, and overall visual appearance of web pages.
  - Enables the separation of content (HTML) from presentation (CSS), improving maintainability.
  - Supports responsive design, allowing web pages to adapt to different screen sizes and devices.
  - Provides various features like selectors, box model, flexbox, grid, animations, and transitions.
  - Enhances user experience by enabling rich, visually appealing designs.

nodes.title: TailwindCSS
nodes.description:
#### Tailwind CSS ***is*** a 
utility-first CSS framework **that** provides a set of classes for quickly styling your web pages.
  - Enables fast development by applying classes directly in your HTML.
  - Highly customizable through a configuration file.
  - Supports responsive design with built-in utilities.
  - Avoids common CSS issues like specificity conflicts.
  - Ideal for building custom designs efficiently.

nodes.title: NPM
nodes.description:
#### NPM ***is*** a 
package manager for JavaScript **that** is used to install, share, and manage dependencies for projects.
  - Stands for Node Package Manager.
  - Comes bundled with Node.js, making it an essential tool for JavaScript developers.
  - Provides a vast registry of packages, enabling code reuse and modular development.
  - Allows developers to publish their own packages and collaborate with others.
  - Supports semantic versioning, ensuring compatibility and stability of dependencies.
  - Facilitates scripts for automating tasks like testing, building, and deploying applications.

nodes.title: React
nodes.description:
#### React.js ***is*** a 
JavaScript library **that** is used for building user interfaces, particularly single-page applications.
  - Developed and maintained by Facebook.
  - Uses a component-based architecture, allowing for reusable and modular UI components.
  - Implements a virtual DOM to optimize rendering and improve performance.
  - Supports JSX, a syntax extension that allows writing HTML-like code within JavaScript.
  - Manages application state effectively with hooks and context.
  - Integrates well with other libraries and frameworks, making it versatile for various projects.
  - Ideal for creating fast, interactive, and scalable front-end applications.

nodes.title: Vue
nodes.description:
#### Vue.js ***is*** a 
progressive JavaScript framework **that** is used for building user interfaces and single-page applications.
  - Designed to be incrementally adoptable, integrating easily with other projects and libraries.
  - Utilizes a component-based architecture for building reusable UI components.
  - Supports reactive data binding and a virtual DOM for efficient updates.
  - Includes features like directives, computed properties, and watchers for handling complex UI logic.
  - Provides a CLI and a rich ecosystem of tools and libraries for enhancing development.
  - Ideal for developing dynamic and interactive web applications with ease.

nodes.title: JQuery
nodes.description:
#### jQuery ***is*** a 
fast, small, and feature-rich JavaScript library **that** simplifies HTML document traversal, event handling, and animation.
  - Makes it easier to use JavaScript on your website.
  - Provides a simple syntax for selecting elements and manipulating the DOM.
  - Includes features for handling events, making AJAX requests, and creating animations.
  - Compatible with all major browsers, ensuring cross-browser compatibility.
  - Extensible with plugins, allowing for additional functionality.
  - Ideal for adding interactivity and dynamic behavior to web pages with minimal code.

nodes.title: Angular
nodes.description:
#### Angular ***is*** a 
platform and framework for building single-page client applications using HTML and TypeScript.
  - Developed and maintained by Google.
  - Uses a component-based architecture for building scalable and maintainable applications.
  - Includes features like data binding, dependency injection, and routing.
  - Supports development of complex applications with a rich set of built-in tools and libraries.
  - Provides a CLI for efficient project setup, development, and deployment.
  - Ideal for developing dynamic, high-performance web applications.

nodes.title: Next js
nodes.description:
#### Next.js ***is*** a 
React framework **that** enables server-side rendering and static site generation for building web applications.
  - Developed and maintained by Vercel.
  - Supports both server-side rendering (SSR) and static site generation (SSG), improving performance and SEO.
  - Provides an intuitive file-based routing system.
  - Includes built-in CSS and Sass support, with options for CSS-in-JS solutions.
  - Features API routes to create API endpoints as part of the application.
  - Ideal for building fast, SEO-friendly, and scalable web applications.

nodes.title: Vuex
nodes.description:
#### Vuex ***is*** a 
state management library **that** is used for managing and centralizing state in Vue.js applications.
  - Serves as a single source of truth for the application's state.
  - Facilitates communication between components by storing and managing state in a centralized store.
  - Supports reactive data binding and ensures that state changes are efficiently propagated to components.
  - Integrates seamlessly with Vue.js, leveraging its reactivity system.
  - Includes features like mutations, actions, getters, and modules for organizing state management logic.
  - Ideal for large-scale applications where managing state across multiple components can be complex.

nodes.title: Vite
nodes.description:
#### Vite ***is*** a 
next-generation front-end build tool **that** offers an extremely fast development experience.
  - Developed by Evan You, the creator of Vue.js.
  - Uses native ES modules for development, enabling instant server start and fast hot module replacement (HMR).
  - Bundles code with Rollup for production, ensuring optimized builds.
  - Supports out-of-the-box configuration for popular frameworks like Vue, React, and Svelte.
  - Provides a rich plugin API for extending functionality.
  - Ideal for modern web development, improving efficiency and reducing build times.

nodes.title: Webpack
nodes.description:
#### Webpack ***is*** a 
powerful module bundler **that** is used for bundling JavaScript files and other assets for web applications.
  - Transforms front-end assets such as HTML, CSS, and images, as well as JavaScript.
  - Allows developers to use modular code and bundle it into a single file or smaller files.
  - Supports code splitting, lazy loading, and dynamic imports for optimized performance.
  - Utilizes loaders to preprocess files and plugins to extend its capabilities.
  - Provides a robust ecosystem of plugins and loaders for various tasks.
  - Ideal for building complex web applications with optimized performance and maintainable code.

nodes.title: Jest
nodes.description:
#### Jest ***is*** a 
JavaScript testing framework **that** is built for simplicity and speed.
  - Developed by Facebook and maintained by the community.
  - Known for its zero-configuration setup, requiring minimal setup to start writing tests.
  - Supports testing of JavaScript code, including React, Vue, Angular, and Node.js applications.
  - Includes built-in assertion library and mocking capabilities for testing dependencies.
  - Provides parallel test execution, making it fast and scalable.
  - Integrates easily with CI/CD pipelines and other tools for automated testing.
  - Ideal for writing unit tests, integration tests, and snapshot tests with ease.

nodes.title: Jasmine
nodes.description:
#### Jasmine ***is*** a 
behavior-driven development (BDD) framework **that** is used for testing JavaScript code.
  - Provides a clean syntax for defining tests with descriptive names and expectations.
  - Supports testing asynchronous code with built-in mechanisms like `async` and `await`.
  - Includes a built-in assertion library for writing expectations.
  - Integrates with various test runners and frameworks.
  - Generates detailed and readable test reports.
  - Ideal for writing clear and maintainable tests for JavaScript applications.

nodes.title: Cypress
nodes.description:
#### Cypress ***is*** a 
modern end-to-end testing framework **that** is built for the web.
  - Provides a fast, reliable, and easy-to-use testing experience.
  - Allows developers to write tests using JavaScript or TypeScript.
  - Offers automatic waiting and retrying for elements, making tests more resilient to timing issues.
  - Provides real-time test execution with interactive debugging and snapshots.
  - Supports testing across different browsers and devices.
  - Integrates seamlessly with CI/CD pipelines for continuous testing.
  - Ideal for testing web applications comprehensively, from UI interactions to backend integrations.

nodes.title: Three js
nodes.description:
#### Three.js ***is*** a 
JavaScript library **that** is used for creating 3D graphics and animations in web browsers.
  - Provides a simple API for working with WebGL, allowing developers to create complex 3D scenes.
  - Includes a wide range of features such as geometries, materials, lights, textures, and animations.
  - Supports virtual reality (VR) and augmented reality (AR) applications through WebXR.
  - Offers a large community and ecosystem with numerous examples and extensions.
  - Ideal for building interactive 3D visualizations, games, simulations, and virtual environments on the web.

nodes.title: WebGL
nodes.description:
#### WebGL ***is*** a 
JavaScript API **that** allows rendering interactive 3D and 2D graphics within any compatible web browser.
  - Based on OpenGL ES, providing high-performance graphics rendering capabilities.
  - Enables hardware-accelerated rendering using the GPU for improved performance.
  - Utilizes shaders written in GLSL (OpenGL Shading Language) for customizing rendering pipelines.
  - Supports complex visual effects, animations, and interactive experiences directly in web applications.
  - Widely used for creating games, simulations, data visualizations, and virtual reality (VR) applications on the web.
